HEADWORD: Xylem
<hw>Xy"lem</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <grk>xy`lon</grk>
wood.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>That portion of a fibrovascular
bundle which has developed, or will develop, into wood cells; --
distinguished from <contr>phloem</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Xylene</ent>⟦br⟧
